{"title":"BMC Expands Teammachine SLR Family — Lighter, Faster, Built for More Riders","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bmc-teammachine-slr-road-bik/","date":1773415756000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Photo/BMC\" /></p>\n<p>For years, the BMC Teammachine has defined what many riders expect from a modern race bike. Long before the industry started blending climbing bikes with aero machines, BMC’s flagship platform was already doing both. It was one of the original “do-everything-bikes”. The Teammachine has won Monuments, Grand Tour stages, and plenty of local races along the way. Now, BMC is expanding the Teammachine SLR family with a lighter frame, improved aerodynamics, and a wider range of carbon options designed to bring that performance to more riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side-.jpg\"><img width=\"2512\" height=\"1675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 three side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side-.jpg 2512w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-side--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(All photos/BMC)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>BMC Teammachine SLR – What’s New? </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The concept behind the latest generation is simple, and what all brands are trying to pull off: build a bike that excels everywhere. Simple, and yet – it’s probably one of the hardest things to do. There are so many trade-offs, and finding the correct balance is nearly impossible, so you have to aim at who the target rider is and what they are looking to accomplish. Since the Teammachine SLR has always been about performance and performance-focused riders. The BMC team focused on the big three pillars of performance metrics that define a race bike: weight, stiffness, and aerodynamics. <br /><br /><em>The question is, can they tweak all three and still maintain a bike that rides like the Teammachine without getting lost in the data? </em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine duo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-duo-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>A Drop in Weight</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Weight reduction was one of the main targets for the new Teammachine SLR. But as BMC is quick to point out, lowering weight alone isn’t enough. In performance bikes, the real metric that matters is stiffness-<strong><em>to</em></strong>-weight ratio, the balance between structural rigidity and overall mass.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Teammachine SLR 01 frameset drops 222 grams compared to the previous generation, representing a 16% reduction in weight while maintaining the same stiffness levels.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>BMC achieved the reduction by having engineers select new, stiffer carbon materials, refine tube shapes throughout the frame, and even minimize the graphics package to eliminate unnecessary grams. The result is a frame that’s lighter without sacrificing the crisp power transfer riders expect from a race bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-.jpg\"><img width=\"940\" height=\"1160\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-.jpg 940w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01--243x300.jpg 243w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01--97x120.jpg 97w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01--768x948.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Closing the Aero Gap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While the Teammachine SLR has traditionally been BMC’s lightweight all-rounder, the brand has steadily added aerodynamic refinement to the platform. Historically, the Teammachine SLR and the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/one-ride-review-bmc-teammachine-r-road-race-bike/\">Teammachine R </a>(reviewed here) were clearly separated by their aerodynamic profiles. The R model was the dedicated aero machine, while the SLR focused primarily on weight and handling.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>That distinction still exists, but the gap has narrowed significantly.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Through refined tube shapes, reduced frontal area, and improved integration, the newest generation of the Teammachine SLR has closed the gap between itself and the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bmcs-latest-premium-teammachine-r-mpc-road-bike-is-a-more-affordable-masterpiece/\">Teammachine R</a> to just 4%.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars-.jpg\"><img width=\"1728\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 back bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars-.jpg 1728w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-back-bars--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>How, you ask? </em></strong>The frame tubes themselves have been reshaped to reduce drag without adding unnecessary mass. BMC also integrated aerodynamic bottle cages designed to work in conjunction with the frame’s airflow profile. The bottle cage takes aero and non-aero bottles, FYI. These details may seem small individually, but together they reduce turbulence and improve efficiency.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side-.png\"><img width=\"1382\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side-.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side-.png 1382w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side--297x184.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side--120x74.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-top-side--768x475.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another key component is the ICS Carbon Aero cockpit. It neatly and cleanly integrates cables and hoses while optimizing airflow at the front of the bike. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bmc-ics2-carbon-aero-mpc-ics-carbon-xc-cockpits/\"><em>You can get this cockpit separately, but if you’re paying that much, you might as well buy the whole bike.</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset-.jpg\"><img width=\"1728\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 three crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset-.jpg 1728w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-crankset--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tuned Compliance Concept Returns</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the defining characteristics of the Teammachine platform has always been its ride feel. BMC has long focused on balancing stiffness with comfort, and the newest generation continues that way.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far-.jpg\"><img width=\"2489\" height=\"1659\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine far\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far-.jpg 2489w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-far--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame retains the company’s Tuned Compliance Concept (TCC), a design approach that uses carefully engineered frame flex to absorb road vibration without sacrificing power transfer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most visible component of this system is the dropped seat stay design, in which the seat stays intersect the seat tube lower than in traditional designs. This configuration allows the rear triangle to flex slightly under load, helping to dissipate vibration from rough roads.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action-.jpg\"><img width=\"2468\" height=\"1646\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine action\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action-.jpg 2468w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-action--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/BMC)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>According to BMC, the newest Teammachine SLR retains 100% compliance with the previous generation, despite significant weight reduction and aerodynamic improvements. In practical terms, that means the bike maintains its ability to smooth out rough pavement while still feeling precise and responsive when power is applied.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup.jpg\"><img width=\"2325\" height=\"1550\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup.jpg 2325w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-closeup-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tweaked Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Handling has always been a defining feature of the Teammachine series. Rather than dramatically altering geometry with each generation, BMC has refined a formula that prioritizes balance and predictability.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Teammachine SLR maintains a consistent 63mm trail figure across all frame sizes, a number the company has optimized over many years of development. By keeping the trail number consistent across sizes, BMC ensures that riders experience the same handling characteristics whether they’re on a smaller or larger frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart-.png\"><img width=\"1054\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart-.png\" alt=\"BMC SLR Teammachine Geo Chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart-.png 1054w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart--297x182.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart--120x74.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-SLR-Teammachine-Geo-Chart--768x471.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This approach creates a bike that feels stable at high speeds but remains nimble when navigating technical roads or tight corners. Interestingly, the geometry mirrors that used on the Teammachine R, reinforcing the idea that the two bikes now share much of the same racing DNA.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side-.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 two back side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side--720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-back-side-.jpg 1728w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars-.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 three bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars--720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-bars-.jpg 1728w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Expanding the Carbon Platform</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Perhaps the most notable change for the new generation is the expansion of the Teammachine SLR lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>BMC now offers the bike in three carbon constructions:</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>01 Premium Carbon</strong></em><br />This is the flagship frame construction. It uses BMC’s most advanced carbon layup and a lightweight paint application to achieve the best possible stiffness-to-weight ratio.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>01 Pro Carbon</em></strong><br />A slightly less weight-optimized construction that maintains the same ride characteristics while using a standard paint finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Advanced Carbon</em></strong><br />The most accessible version of the Teammachine platform. While it uses a different carbon layup, it retains the core geometry and ride feel that define the SLR family.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC.png\"><img width=\"1410\" height=\"724\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC.png 1410w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-297x153.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-120x62.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-768x394.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Modular Cockpit Integration</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>BMC’s integrated cockpit system has also evolved with the new Teammachine SLR. The frames are compatible with any ICS cockpit configuration, including both one-piece integrated bars and traditional stem-and-handlebar setups.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC.jpeg\"><img width=\"1108\" height=\"690\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC.jpeg\" alt=\"ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC.jpeg 1108w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC-297x185.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-BMC-768x478.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"875\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces-1536x875.jpeg\" alt=\"BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces-1536x875.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces-297x169.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces-768x438.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BMC-ICS2-Carbon-Aero-MPC-pieces.jpeg 1576w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Top-tier builds come equipped with the second-generation ICS Carbon Aero cockpit, which offers multiple handlebar widths and stem length combinations. This modular approach allows riders to fine-tune their fit while maintaining the aerodynamic benefits of cable integration.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs-.jpg\"><img width=\"2510\" height=\"1673\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine legs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs-.jpg 2510w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-legs--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated Seatpost and Offsets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Teammachine SLR also introduces updated AeroShape seatposts, designed to balance aerodynamic efficiency with fit flexibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Seatposts are offered in three offsets:</em></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>0mm offset for smaller frame sizes (47–51)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>10mm offset for mid to large sizes (54–61)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>25mm offset available aftermarket</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This system ensures riders can achieve their optimal saddle position regardless of frame size.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side-.jpg\"><img width=\"1743\" height=\"1035\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 two full side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side-.jpg 1743w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side--297x176.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side--1536x912.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side--120x71.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-two-full-side--768x456.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>BMC Teammachine SLR – Pricing and Range</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Teammachine SLR 01 Premium Carbon</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Teammachine SLR 01 ONE — $14,599 USD / €12,999<br />Teammachine SLR 01 TWO — $13,499 USD / €11,999<br />Teammachine SLR 01 THREE — $9,499 USD / €8,499</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side-.jpg\"><img width=\"1758\" height=\"1006\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 three full side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side-.jpg 1758w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side--297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side--1536x879.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side--120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-three-full-side--768x439.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Teammachine SLR 01 Pro Carbon</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SLR 01 FOUR — $10,999 USD / €8,999<br />SLR 01 FIVE — $8,399 USD / €7,499<br />SLR 01 SIX — $7,299 USD / €6,499<br />SLR 01 SEVEN — $6,199 USD / €5,499</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side-.jpg\"><img width=\"1759\" height=\"1012\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side-.jpg\" alt=\"BMC Teammachine SRL 01 side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side-.jpg 1759w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side--297x171.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side--1536x884.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side--120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/BMC-Teammachine-SRL-01-side--768x442.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Teammachine SLR Advanced Carbon</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SLR ONE — $4,799 USD / €3,999<br />SLR TWO — $3,599 USD / €2,999<br />SLR THREE — $2,899 USD / €2,499</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://us.bmc-switzerland.com/?gad_source=1&amp;gad_campaignid=22691441267&amp;gbraid=0AAAAA-ve-CE2o3JRIvaLwRKy8cW-wkHQj&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjwyMnNBhBNEiwA-Kcgu1iPu8SXEXvkcBAkUhkJ9RcT5fCxxR3qr6dm1DN-hgqa3HlAmPxj3xoCPkMQAvD_BwE\">More info at BMC</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bmc-teammachine-slr-road-bik/\">BMC Expands Teammachine SLR Family — Lighter, Faster, Built for More Riders</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a39f4bb144dbbadfa5a31e917704025333f6a274ec6597f585115d99265f3128","category":"Cycling"}